    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-26T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="429"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/11–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-26T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 26, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>649. Please give the Iranian Government a copy of the note to the Soviet
                    Government contained in the Department’s telegram No. 644, November 23, 5
                        p.m.<note n="70" xml:id="d429fn70">Same as No. 10209 to London, <ref
                            target="#pg_450">p. 450</ref>.</note> The text is being released to the
                    press here today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
